This scrip download the source from wine-tkg-6.17.r0.g5f19a815 release
The generated package will be installed in /opt so that is can be installed
with another wine in /usr

These are not addressed for now, to integrate with desktop
symbolic link to wine64 and wine from home should work
/usr/share/applications/
/usr/bin/

Installing multilib for Slackware 15 is enough to build

you most install 32-bit boots for example from this link:
https://mirrors.slackware.com/slackware/slackware-15.0/slackware/l/boost-1.78.0-i586-1.txz

and run:
convertpkg-compat32 -i boost-1.78.0-i586-1.txz
installpkg /tmp/boost-compat32-1.78.0-x86_64-1compat32.txz
